menu "BT LE Audio TX"

config TX_TGT_LEAD_TIME_US
	prompt "Target lead time to send data to controller before the controller send the next SDU"
	int
	default 3000
	help
	  Do not change this value unless you know what you are doing.
	  Will likely need to be changed for ISO intervals unequal to 10 ms.
	  This is the target lead time to send data to controller before it sends the next SDU on air.
	  This is used to make sure that the data is sent to controller just in time for the next SDU, which can help with reducing the overall latency and power consumption.
	  Setting this too low may lead to flushed data, and too high will increase latency.

config TX_LEAD_TIME_DEVIATION_US
	prompt "Max allowed deviation in microseconds from TX_TGT_LEAD_TIME_US"
	int
	range 500 TX_TGT_LEAD_TIME_US
	default 2500
	help
	  Do not change this value unless you know what you are doing.
	  Will likely need to be changed for ISO intervals unequal to 10 ms.
	  This deviation may take into account audio processing jitter,
	  which can be caused by e.g. variable encoding time.
	  Modules may use this value in different ways.


endmenu # BT LE Audio TX